               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18451027-name-1294" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1294" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1294" type="surname" value="PENTLETON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1294" type="given" value="ABRAHAM"></interp>ABRAHAM PENTLETON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am watchman of Vauxhall-gardens. There was a grea't quantity of zinc pipe about the gardens—we have missed thirty or forty feet of it—it belonged to Mr. Frederick Giles when he was the manager there—the place belongs to Mr. Robert Wardle and others—I believe this to be some of that pipe—I have no doubt of it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18451027-name-1295" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1295" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1295" type="surname" value="HOWSON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18451027-name-1295" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM HOWSON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a marine-store dealer, and live in Vauxhall-street. On the 29th of Oct. the prisoner brought a piece of iron to me—he gave me his address—he returned, and asked me if I bought zinc pipe—I said yes—he went away, and I communicated with an officer, knowing there had been some lost from the gardens—the prisoner brought this pipe, and the officer took him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I picked it up in Moss fields.</p>
